They passed a check in Alava in a van with 2,000 kilos of hashish .
Ten minutes to five.
The road inspection of Ertzaintza in the municipal district of Armiñón (Álava).
The officers stop two people in a van and they run away.
A shipment of more than two tons of hashish is unstoppable.
According to the report of the Department of the Interior of the Basque Government, the officers pursued and detained one of the persons in the van, a man of 38 years, who was identified as A. A. J.
The man in custody has been charged with drug trafficking and forging government documents.
The incident occurred when several members of the Transport Unit were conducting a road check on the N-1 in places where it crosses the border of the Armiñón city district.
They were about to stop the van for a check, but the driver disobeyed instructions, accelerated sharply, and drove off.
The authorities immediately began to pursue the vehicle, and when it came to a stop on the side of the road a few miles away, both passengers jumped out and fled into the forest.
The Ertzaint agents eventually caught up with one of them and confiscated 2,178 kilograms of hashish that the suspects were transporting, as revealed during a search of an Iveco Daily van.
The back of the vehicle was loaded with packets of hashish, which were then transported to other police departments for detailed expertise and weighing of the drugs.
