Defending the traditional cinema is a topic that has always been important: the closing of the Super Cinema in Bagheri, the place of my childhood and adolescence, was the spark that convinced me to found the "New Cinema Paradiso", which I had been thinking about for 10 years.
I've lived in Rome for 25 years, and when I walk past the Rialtes or Quirinale on the Rue Nazionale, where I shared so much emotion, so as not to have to look at the black dust signs, I turn the other way.
